&lt;p&gt;When adding a new Remote Desktop connection using the official Microsoft Mac App Store

&lt;a target=&#34;_blank&#34; href=&#34;https://itunes.apple.com/en/app/microsoft-remote-desktop/id715768417?mt=12&#34;&gt;Remote Desktop&lt;/a&gt; &lt;i class=&#34;fa fa-external-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; app
on my MacBook, the default value for full screen mode is to use all available monitors.
This results in a few pixels missing on top of the screen. Disabling this option will fix this issue.&lt;/p&gt;
